added.title: Second Christmas
added.description: The Titans trick Starfire into believing in second Christmas with second Santa.

added.title: Beast Boy on a Shelf
added.description: Santa Claus forces Beast Boy to become a spy and report on the Titans' naughty behavior.

added.title: Christmas Crusaders
added.description: Santa Claus and Robin must stop the nefarious Coal Miner.

added.title: The Coach
added.description: The new coach at Elmore High stands up to Jamie. The new Coach witnesses Jamie bullying the other kids at lunch and steps in. Jamie is made to apologise, much to the amazement of the other kids. Gumball and Darwin worry about Jamie seeking revenge, especially when they see him sneaking into the back of Coach's car. They use their newly acquired gym skills to save the Coach from being bullied.

added.title: The Countdown
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are running late for school but need to arrive in time to avoid expulsion. Gumball and Darwin hit snooze too many times on their alarm clock and miss the school-bus. Miss Simian has threatened to expel them if they don't get to school on time. A mysterious clock appears showing exactly how long they have to get to school. When it looks like they aren't going to make it in time, they stop the clock which effects the space/time continuum.

added.title: The Downer
added.description: Gumball is in a funk that is proving hard to shake. Gumball refuses to get out of bed because he is in a lousy mood. When his family try to cheer him up Gumball wishes they'd all just disappear and, inexplicably, they do. At first he enjoys the solitude and doing just as he pleases but soon his mood threatens to take control of him completely.

added.title: Sleepover at JP's
added.description: JP invites his friends over for a sleepover, but it happens to be on the night of a huge game of Flashlight Tag in the Creek!

added.title: The Cardboard Identity
added.description: Craig and his friends stumble upon a mysterious bunker made of cardboard beneath the Creek.

added.title: Mortimor to the Rescue
added.description: When Craig, Kelsey and JP get stranded in murky water, it's up to Mortimor to save the day!

added.title: Trading Day
added.description: After Craig accidentally destroys a shipment of rare Chocorolls at the Trading Tree, Kit makes him work off his debt by running her trades throughout the Creek!

added.title: Kelsey the Worthy
added.description: When Kelsey demolishes a wall at Craig's house, her father takes away her sword. So she enlists Craig and JP to help prove to her father that she's still worthy.

added.title: Encore'tney
added.description: When Courtney turns to a magical datebook to help her achieve perfection, she's trapped in a never ending loop until a friend teaches her a valuable lesson.

added.title: Las Pesadillas
added.description: When Vic and Val experience a mysterious nightmare that turns deadly, they realize they must stop a sinister force from enchanting them to sleep forever.

added.title: Baby Pepito
added.description: When a mysterious "baby" appears on Chata's doorstep, V&V are convinced it's not what it seems.

added.title: Cenote Seekers
added.description: When Vic and Val are running too late to get a ride from Xochi to a fun water park cenote on a particularly hot day, they instead take their bikes. But they wind up lost in the desert and start to hallucinate while blaming each other for getting into this mess.

added.title: Lowlifes
added.description: Apple & Onion cannot allow themselves to be viewed by society- and more importantly by smug old Chicken Nugget-as lowlifes.

added.title: Falafel's Car Keys
added.description: Apple & Onion are deemed responsible enough to borrow Falafel's car for their first road trip together. Nothing will go wrong, and they're going to make sure of that… by getting some practice in.

added.title: Apple's in Trouble
added.description: Apple is challenged to a fight by a grumpy Cheesesteak, so he and Onion go on a quest to find the source of Cheesesteak's grumpiness.

added.title: 4 on 1
added.description: Onion's fear of crowds threatens his basketball team's success.

added.title: Moor Fogg
added.description: Team Tennyson goes international in the Omni-Copter and the first stop is for a hike in the Scottish Highlands, but the weather isn't just bad, it's foggy, and that means one thing and one thing only: the return of The Fogg!

added.title: Speechless on the Seine
added.description: While in Paris, France, Ben catches Zombozo robbing the Louvre, but when Zombozo hypnotizes Ben to remain speechless, Ben must navigate a foreign land like a mime in order to stop the criminal clown and his travelling circus.

added.title: Big in Japan
added.description: During a tour of the Japanese Robotics Museum, Ben finds hero-gone-wrong Tim Buktu "trying to save" Tokyo from a Dragon. Has Tim finally turned over a new leaf, or is this just another one of his half-baked plans to play the part of hero?

added.title: Big Ben 10
added.description: When Ben and family go to London to visit the legendary Big Ben, the Bugg Brothers are there to greet them, with yet another outrageously over the top plan of course: to shrink the Big Ben bell in order to steal it!

added.title: Lickety Split
added.description: When a mysterious electrical storm downs the Omni-Copter at the Equator, Team Tennyson soon discovers Solar & Polar are behind it, but when Ben accidentally combines the two into a more powerful Uni-Twin, our hero must think fast if he is going to save the planet!

added.title: Chaotic Clumping
added.description: Elliott and Mo accidentally take a teleporter together, and find themselves closer than they've ever been before. Will they decide to mutually part ways?

added.title: Parallel Paradox
added.description: Elliott finds himself having to be in two places at once.

added.title: #SheMightBeGiant
added.description: Karen Beecher is always getting picked on at school, but when the local mall is attacked by a monstrous supervillain called Giganta, she discovers that tiny Bumblebee might be the only one small enough to save the day.

added.title: #FightAtTheMuseum
added.description: Supergirl always relies on her strength, but she'll need more than brawn to stop brainy Catwoman from stealing valuable gems from the local science museum.

added.title: #FromBatToWorse
added.description: Having just moved to the boring Metropolis suburbs, Batgirl is thrilled when she intercepts a call from Batman asking for help. But before she can stop a visiting Gotham villain, she'll have to sneak past her dad, Police Commissioner Gordon.

added.title: #CrushingIt
added.description: Diana Prince is absolutely crushing it in every single aspect of life as a student at Metropolis High, until someone shows up who threatens to throw her off her game for good.

added.title: Lost in the Lost and Found
added.description: When Boss sends Tiggy and Gweeseek into the cellar to fetch a tuba, Tiggy must be brave and overcome his fears of the "Cellar Feller."

added.title: Baby and the Dog
added.description: On a mission to find an orange tennis ball, Tig and Seek encounter their worst nightmares: a baby and a dog. Do they have what it takes to go up against this gruesome twosome and walk away with their ball?

added.title: Burrito
added.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

added.title: Now We're Only Falling Apart
added.description: Pearl tells a story.

added.title: What's Your Problem?
added.description: Amethyst convinces Steven to take a day off for himself.

added.title: The Question
added.description: Steven shows some city slicker gems how the cowboys lived.

added.title: Made of Honor
added.description: Steven has a big surprise for the Crystal Gems.

added.title: Reunited
added.description: Steven brings everyone together for a special reunion.

added.title: Driller
added.description: Panthro is getting a little fed up with having to fix things around the Cats' Lair constantly, which is unfortunate because the ThunderCats are about to be attacked by an unstoppable drilling robot, and he's gonna break everything!

added.title: Secret of the Unicorn
added.description: A crying unicorn appears at the Cats' Lair and weepily tells the ThunderCats that all of her unicorn friends have been captured! Tygra thinks he's just the unicorn expert to help the last of the unicorns, he just needs her to stop sobbing long enough to tell him who took her friends. Easier said than done.

added.title: Panthro Plagiarized!
added.description: Vultureman has got a brand new invention but there's one big problem: he stole the idea from Panthro! Oh, also Vultureman is using his invention to take over Third Earth. So, there are two big problems.

added.title: Warrior Maiden Invasion
added.description: Third Earth is being overrun by super tough, super buff Warrior Maidens and it looks like the ThunderCats are next on their hit list! It's gonna be up to the ThunderKittens to save the day even though the kittens are so small and the Warrior Maidens are so big.

added.title: Lost Sword
added.description: Lion-O is reminded that he needs to plug the Sword of Omens into the Cats' Lair each night or else the base will run out of power. That's fine, it's not like Lion-O's going to accidentally lose the sword or anything. Right?

added.title: The Speedway Five-Billion
added.description: Unagami's soldiers, the Red Visors, finally discover the secret location of Scott's garage and attack the ninja, who manage to escape with the help of Racer Seven, and enter the spectacular Speedway Five Billion.

added.title: Stop, Drop and Side Scroll
added.description: Our ninja barely have time to mourn the loss of their fallen ninja friends before being thrust into the madness of Terra Domina where Lloyd will have to face an old adversary from his past.

added.title: Ninjago Confidential
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, Zane and Pixal hit the mean streets to track down Milton Dyer, only to discover that things are not what they seem.

added.title: The Prodigal Father
added.description: Zane, kidnapped by the Mechanic, faces Unagami. Master Wu fights to free Zane, while Pixal questions Milton Dyer for information on how to shut down Prime Empire.

added.title: The Temple of Madness
added.description: Jay must stand alone against Unagami in the end-game, yet Unagami has a bigger battle in facing the truth about his own identity.

added.title: Ultraclops
added.description: Badgerclops gets huge to destroy a towering monster, but when he refuses to shrink down, the kingdom faces a new terror.

added.title: Not Impressed
added.description: When a Sweetypie isn't impressed with the sheriff dept's antics, our three heroes try everything to win him over.

added.title: I Am My Monster
added.description: Everything is not fine.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.title: The Scratch Pack
added.description: Axel and the team must run damage control after a loose spark of Minergy accidentally turns Zoe's old toys - a set of cute squishy kittens - into a pack of snarling beasts.

added.title: Knockout
added.description: Axel and the team juggle not waking Uncle Andrew from his nap and stopping Orangutank from stealing Andrew's latest invention: the Knockout Box!

added.title: Sarge in Charge
added.description: Axel and the team must rescue Sarge Charge from a solo mission in the backyard, which Orangutank has turned into his own personal heart of darkness.

added.title: The Other Side
added.description: Axel must 'save' Bobbie Blobby after she defects to Madcap's team, tempted by Porcupunk and his assertion that she belongs with the bad toys.

added.title: Bear-Knuckle Brawl
added.description: Axel must team up with Bearbarian to stop Madcap from transforming Luka's stuffed bear collection into an invincible army.

added.title: The Awesome Brawlers vs. Haavik/Their Fights
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers vs. Haavik: Dan and the Awesome brawlers have made their way up Haavik's tower as the final showdown between Haavik and the Awesome Brawlers begins./Their Fights: Haavik's Bakugan battle league rages on in an ultimate showdown between the Awesome Brawlers, vs Haavik and his destructive friends.

added.title: Haavik's Final Show/Miracle Planet
added.description: Haavik's Final Show: It's the final stage of Haavik's Bakugan Battle League: Dan and Drago Infinity vs. Haavik and his six-faction fusion Bakugan, Sabrus. Once again, the fate of two worlds, Earth and Vestoria rests in the hands of the Awesome Brawlers!/ Miracle Planet: The epic clash between Drago Infinty and Sabrus rages on. The winner of this clash of titans will decide the fate Earth and Vestroia.

added.title: Origin of Species
added.description: Origin of Species, Part 1: Dan meets his partner Bakugan Drago for the first time and we learn about the incident that happened on Earth twelve years ago./Origin of Species, Part 2: Dan and friends win the Bakugan Battle, firmly establishing the Awesome Ones as our heroes and Bakugan Brawlers.

added.title: Burger Run/Monkey See, Monkey Don't
added.description: Burger Run: When the local Burger Joint is being threatened by a rogue Bakugan, Dan steps up to save the day and the burgers!/Monkey See, Monkey Don't: The AO stop neighborhood kids from copycat behavior (namely, using their Bakugan for frivolous reasons).

added.title: Bully for You/Trolling for Laughs
added.description: Bully for You: The AO must handle a neighborhood bully who is using his Bakugan to pick on the local kids./Trolling for Laughs: Wynton's constant practical jokes wear thin on his Bakugan Trox so the Bakugan decide to teach him a lesson.

added.title: Guardian of the Unikingdom
added.description: Hawkodile insists the Unikingdom is more dangerous than it looks and sets out to prove it by taking his friends on bodyguard patrol.

added.title: Cast Aside the Truth
added.description: Hawkodile breaks his arm in a careless spill and lies to his friends about the accident to keep from looking bad.

added.title: Unikitty and the Ice Pop Factory
added.description: An eccentric figure announces a contest to tour her marvelous ice pop factory, sending the gang on a frantic quest to find the winning popsicle stick.

added.title: Soda Genie
added.description: When KO, Rad, and Enid find a soda bottle with a genie in it, they get more than they bargained for.

added.title: Boxman Crashes
added.description: Lord Boxman crashes at Venomous' lair and inserts himself into his villainous affairs.

added.title: Plaza Alone
added.description: It's KO's birthday, and Rad and Enid want to make sure everything goes perfectly.

added.title: Monster Party
added.description: Enid is faced with a choice when her old friends from Ghoul School show up.

added.title: Super Black Friday
added.description: After being forced to work on a holiday, KO, Rad and Enid take a stand.

added.title: Ragnarock and Roll
added.description: When an ancient prophecy spells doom for Townsville, the girls must race to stop it.

added.title: Brain Freeze
added.description: When a mysterious new ice cream flavor takes Townsville by storm, the girls suspect there might be foul play.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 1
added.description: Now on his own, Ben sets out to be a solo superhero, with new alien heroes at his disposal, but Grandpa Max has other plans. (Introducing Rook, Malware, Khyber, Nemetrix alien Crabdozer, new Ben aliens Feedback & Blox, Pakmar.)

added.title: A Jolt from the Past
added.description: Alien pests from Ben's youth come back, but now they need Ben's help. (Introducing Fistrick, & new Ben alien Gravattack.)

added.title: It Was Them
added.description: Dr. Animo has escaped his Plumber prison, and Ben and Rook must track him down before he turns the world into his personal mutant ant farm! (Introducing Nemetrix alien Slamworm, Galvan Plumbers Blukic and Driba, Arctiguana, new Ben alien Crashhopper.)

added.title: Tourist Trap
added.description: While messing with the World's Largest Rubberband Ball at a tourist trap, Ben accidently releases some mischievous electrical creatures.

added.title: So Long, and Thanks for All the Smoothies
added.description: When Ben and Rook investigate a mysterious alien ghost ship, they discover that Argit and the Vreedle Brothers are fighting for possession of a doomsday device! (Introducing Solid Plugg.)

added.title: Hot Stretch
added.description: Ben and Rook encounter a race of elastic, hot-blooded aliens in Undertown who want to use a stolen nuclear fusion engine to activate a volcano! (Introducing Ester, Seebik & the Kraaho.)

added.title: The Alliance
added.description: As Fourarms, Ben works to thwart an armored truck robbery by a tough female gang leader named Joey, who delivers a disturbing message from Vilgax.

added.title: Breezy
added.description: With a friendly bee named Breezy as his wingman, Finn decides to get back into the dating game.

added.title: Ahora nos estamos separando
added.description: Perla cuenta una historia.

added.title: Cual es tu problema
added.description: Amatista convence a Steven de que se tome un día libre.

added.title: La pregunta
added.description: Steven les muestra a unas gemas citadinas cómo vivían los vaqueros.

added.title: Dama de honor
added.description: Steven tiene una gran sorpresa para las Gemas de Cristal.

added.title: Reunificados
added.description: Steven reúne a todos para un evento especial.

added.title: Blade of Grass
added.description: Finn and Jake decide it's time for Finn to get a new sword. Finn reluctantly buys a grass sword from a mysterious old man but the sword turns out to be cursed.

added.title: Betty
added.description: In Wizard City, a magic spell backfires and turns Ice King back into Simon.

added.title: Belson's Backpack
added.description: After an accidental backpack swap, Clarence discovers that Belson is hiding an artistic side and attempts to foster Belson's creativity.

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: Pizza Hero
added.description: It's the end of the school year, and as is tradition at Aberdale Elementary, Papa Marianio is slated to dish out his famous pizza along with a spectacle of song and dance. As the kids wait in excitement, they share memories about times with Papa.

added.title: Sumo Goes West
added.description: Clarence learns his best friend Sumo may transfer to another school! It's up to Clarence to protest, petition and rally to convince everyone to let Sumo stay - or face losing his closest school pal!

added.title: La Neblina del Paramo
added.description: El equipo Tennyson se hace internacional en el Omni-Copter, y la primera parada incluye una caminata por las Tierras Altas de Escocia. Pero el clima no es sólo malo, sino que hay niebla, y eso puede significa solamente una cosa: iel regreso de Niebla!

added.title: Insomnio en el Sena
added.description: Durante su estadía en París, Francia, Ben descubre a Zombozo en pleno robo en el Louvre. Pero cuando Zombozo hipnotiza a Ben para que se quede sin palabras, Ben debe navegar por una tierra extranjera como un mimo para detener al payaso criminal y su circo ambulante.

added.title: Grande en Japón
added.description: Durante un recorrido por el Museo de Robótica Japonés, Ben encuentra a Tim Buktu, un héroe que fue por el mal camino, "tratando de salvar" a Tokio de un Dragón. ¿Tim cambió por fin o este no es más que otro de sus planes mal concebido para hacer el papel de héroe?

added.title: Big Ben 10
added.description: Cuando Ben y su familia viajan a Londres para visitar el legendario Big Ben, los hermanos Bicho están allí para darles la bienvenida, obviamente con un nuevo plan escandalosamente exagerado: iencoger la campana del Big Ben para robarla!

added.title: Separacion Rapida
added.description: Cuando una misteriosa tormenta eléctrica se abate sobre el Omni-Copter en el Ecuador, el equipo Tennyson pronto descubre que Solar y Polar están detrás del suceso.

added.title: Taco Comet
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang go undercover to taste the most sought after treat in the cosmos: the Taco Comet.

added.title: The Fan
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's number one fan gets more than he bargained for when Uncle Grandpa overstays his welcome.

added.title: The Status of Cattus
added.description: The Warriors want someone to enjoy collecting Magiswords as much as they do, so they go crazy trying to interest Cattus the Oneblade into obtaining more.

added.title: Team of Broccoli
added.description: The Warrior Family's broccoli crop is stolen and the Warriors and Danelda team up to track it down underground.

added.title: Agent of Destruction
added.description: DeBizz helps the Warriors become more famous as their agent, but Vambre returns to adventuring while Prohyas gets caught up in the DeBizz fame trap.

added.title: Dunkadellic
added.description: After suffering trauma from being the dunk-ee in a dunking booth, Prohyas has trouble getting through the dunk based traps in Man Fish's lair.

added.title: Helping Cattus Help
added.description: The search for a mythical creature gets rather metaphysical when the equally elusive Cattus' assists the mission.

added.title: Pijamada en casa de JP
added.description: JP invita a sus amigos para una pijamada, pero resulta ser la misma noche que un gran juego con linternas en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La identidad de carton
added.description: Craig y sus amigos se topan con un refugio subterráneo hecho de cartón debajo del bosque.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Mortimer al rescate
added.description: Cuando Craig, Kelsey y JP quedan varados en agua turbia, iMortimer debe salir al rescate!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Dia de trueque
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Craig destruye un cargamento de chocolates poco comunes en el árbol del trueque, Kit lo hace trabajar para pagar su deuda: idebe ocuparse de los intercambios de Kit por todo el bosque!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Kelsey la merecedora
added.description: Cuando Kelsey demuele una pared de la casa de Craig, su padre le quita la espada. Por eso, Kelsey les pide ayuda a Craig y a JP para que le demuestren a su padre que aún la merece.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Super Dia de Ofertas
added.description: Cuando los obligan a trabajar en un día festivo, KO, Rad y Enid se pronuncian en contra de la medida.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: El Templo de la Locura
added.description: Jay debe enfrentarse solo a Unagami en el juego final, pero Unagami tiene una batalla más grande al enfrentarse a la verdad sobre su propia identidad.

added.title: Plaza Abandonada
added.description: Es el cumpleaños de KO, y Rad y Enid quieren asegurarse de que todo salga a la perfección.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Fiesta de Monstruos
added.description: Enid debe tomar una decisión cuando llegan sus antiguos amigos de la Escuela de monstruos.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Detenerse, Caer y Girar
added.description: Los Ninjas no han ni llorado la pérdida de sus amigos  caídos cuando ya deben entrar a la locura de Tierra Domina.

added.title: Boxman se Estrella
added.description: Lord Boxman se queda en la guarida de Venomous y se introduce en sus asuntos de villano.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Genio de Soda
added.description: Cuando KO, Rad y Enid encuentran una botella de refresco con un genio en su interior, se llevan más de lo que esperaban.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: El Padre Prodigo
added.description: Zane, secuestrado por el Mecánico mientras Pixal interroga a Milton Dyer para obtener información sobre cómo cerrar el Primer Imperio.

added.title: Carrera Cinco Billones por Hora
added.description: Los soldados de Unagami, los Visores Rojos, finalmente descubren la ubicación secreta del garaje de Scott y atacan a los Ninjas.

added.title: Ninjago Confidencial
added.description: De vuelta en la ciudad de Ninjago, Zane y Pixal salen a las calles para encontrar a Milton Dyer, y descubren que las cosas no son lo que parecen…

added.title: El Origen de las Especies Parte 1
added.description: Dan conoce a su pareja Bakugan, Drago, por primera vez y nos enteramos del "incidente" que ocurrió en la Tierra hace doce años.

added.title: El Origen de las Especies Parte 2
added.description: Dan y sus amigos ganan la Batalla Bakugan, demostrando que los Fantásticos son nuestros héroes y los mejores Peleadores Bakugan.

added.title: Un Almuerzo Inesperado
added.description: Cuando el Restaurante de Hamburguesas es amenazado por un violento Bakugan, Dan llega para salvar el día...y las hamburguesas.

added.title: Una Leccion para Todos
added.description: Los Fantásticos le enseñan a unos chicos del vecindario a no imitar a los demás. Por ejemplo, a quienes utilizan a sus Bakugan con fines frívolos.

added.title: Manzana esta en Problemas
added.description: Bistec con Queso, malhumorado, desafía a Manzana a una pelea. De ese modo, Manzana puede embarcarse con Cebollín en una misión para encontrar el origen del malhumor de Bistec con Queso.

added.title: El Bravucon
added.description: Los Fantásticos deben lidiar con un bravucón que usa a su Bakugan para intimidar a los chicos del vecindario.

added.title: 4 a 1
added.description: El temor de Cebollín a las multitudes amenaza el éxito de su equipo de baloncesto.

added.title: Bromas Pesadas
added.description: Las constantes bromas pesadas de Wynton colman la paciencia de su Bakugan, Trox, quien decide darle una lección.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: A Pardo le gustan los burritos. Mucho. Tanto que cuando un restaurant elabora un Burrito tamaño oso, Pardo se obliga a comer semejante obra de arte majestuosa. Lleva el burrito consigo a todas partes y lo convierte en una parte nueva y cada vez más olorosa de su vida.

added.title: #AunqueSeaGigante
added.description: Karen Beecher siempre es molestada en la escuela. Pero cuando el centro comercial es atacado por una monstruosa super villana llamada Giganta, Karen descubre que la diminuta Bumblebee puede ser la única suficientemente pequeña para salvar el día.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #BatallaEnElMuseo
added.description: Supergirl siempre confía en su fuerza, pero necesitará mas que músculos para impedir que la astuta Catwoman robe unas valiosas gemas del museo de ciencias.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #DeMalEnPeor
added.description: Habiéndose mudado a los aburridos suburbios de Metrópolis, Batgirl se emociona cuando intercepta una llamada de auxilio de Batman. Pero antes de que pueda ir a detener a un villano visitante de Ciudad Gótica, Barbara debe escabullirse de su casa y de su padre, el comisionado Gordon.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #ElFlechazo
added.description: Diana Prince está triunfando en todos los aspectos de la vida y como alumna de la Secundaria Metrópolis... hasta que alguien llega para confundirla totalmente.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: El secreto del unicornio
added.description: Un unicornio que llora aparece en el Cubil Felino y, entre lágrimas, les dice a los Thundercats que todos sus amigos unicornios han sido capturados. Tigro se cree un experto en el tema que podrá ayudar al último de los unicornios...Solo necesita que deje de llorar lo suficiente para decirle quién se llevó a sus amigos. Es más fácil decirlo que hacerlo, viejo.

added.title: Pelea de Nudillos de Oso
added.description: Axel debe formar equipo con Bearbarian para evitar que Madcap transforme la colección de osos de peluche de Luka en un ejército invencible.

added.title: Soy Mi Monstruo
added.description: No todo está bien.

added.title: El Futuro
added.description: Steven por fin está listo para avanzar.

added.title: Ultracolosal
added.description: Colosal se vuelve enorme para destruir a un monstruo altísimo, pero cuando se rehúsa a volver a su tamaño normal, el reino se enfrenta a un nuevo terror… el apetito insaciable de Colosal.

added.title: Nocaut
added.description: Axel y el equipo hacen malabarismos sin despertar al tío Andrew de su siesta y evitar que Orangutank robe el último invento de Andrew: ila Caja Knockout!

added.title: El Otro Lado
